@node "History" "Program History"
@{b}45.11@{ub} (1.10.2014)

 - Updated with IJG jpeglib v9a.
 - Added support for wide gamut colour spaces (JFIF version 2).
 - Improved colour conversion clarity and accuracy.
 - Fixed descriptor file to correctly ignore some non-standard formats
   and unsupported data such as JPEG-LS files.

@{b}45.10@{ub} (7.6.2013)

 - Updated with IJG jpeglib v9.
 - Support lossless files created with improved compression encoder.
 - Support files with invalid component identifiers (created by
   Adobe PDF).

@{b}45.9@{ub} (29.2.2012)

 - Updated with IJG jpeglib v8d.
 - Applications may now configure the datatype settings via a local
   variable, overriding any global user settings present in ENV:.
 - Replaced usage of old Exec and Dos OS4 functions with the new ones.
 - MorphOS and WarpOS versions recompiled with VBCC 0.9b.

@{b}45.8@{ub} (23.2.2011)

 - Updated with IJG jpeglib v8c, which features a SmartScale capable
   decoder which can read images encoded using non-baseline DCT block
   sizes.
 - Added workaround for a bug in OS4 which can cause a crash when a
   requester is opened (bug fixed in intuition.library 53.32).
 - Fixed (VBCC fix) potential system lockup when calling the GM_RENDER
   method in the WarpOS version (e.g. when using Multiview with the
   AfA OS picture.datatype).
 - Added AmiUpdate support.
 - Updated Spanish installer strings.

@{b}45.7@{ub} (5.12.2009)

 - Added workaround for a bug in OS4's datatypes.library
   DTST_MEMORY handling.

@{b}45.6@{ub} (7.11.2009)

 - Updated with IJG jpeglib v7, which includes support for
   arithmetic entropy encoding.
 - Can now load files which contain a non-Exif APP1 marker.
 - Cleaned up WarpDT engine build.
 - Enabled virtual memory usage in OS4 version.
 - MorphOS and WarpOS versions recompiled with VBCC 0.9a.
 - OS4 version recompiled with latest SDK.

@{b}45.5@{ub} (20.1.2006)

 - Fixed descriptor file to handle files with a non-JFIF APP0 marker.
 - Asynchronous i/o now uses dos/SendPkt instead of exec/PutMsg.
 - Updated with the latest WarpDT engine build.
 - MorphOS and WarpOS versions recompiled with VBCC 0.8i.

@{b}45.4@{ub} (18.1.2005)

 - Added native AmigaOS 4 version.
 - Updated with the latest WarpDT engine build.
 - MorphOS and WarpOS versions recompiled with VBCC 0.8g.
 - Added Polish installer translation.
 - Updated Spanish and French installers.

@{b}45.3@{ub} (9.7.2003)

 - Fixed a problem reading the prefs file from disks using FFS.
 - Fixed another bug which caused bogus evaluation period warnings.
 - Tweaked installer so that it checks for picture.datatype in MOSSYS:
   as well as SYS: when run under MorphOS.

@{b}45.2@{ub} (5.7.2003)

 - Fixed problems with the evaluation period code causing bogus warnings.

@{b}45.1@{ub} (4.7.2003)

 - Altered descriptor file to prevent it matching LhA or LZX archives
   containing JPEG files (or anything else that might contain a JFIF
   header, other than JPEG files saved with Photoshop)
 - Minor optimizations and cleanups.
 - Bumped version to v45 since a stable release has now been reached
   and to reflect the jump to @{"shareware" link "Registration" 0} status.

@{b}44.25@{ub} (19.10.2001)

 - Raised minimum WarpUp requirements from V4 to V5, due to cache flush
   bugs in V4 which cause images to be displayed incorrectly (black
   stripes, corrupt images or completely black images).  These bugs
   affected v44.24.  WarpUp V5 does not have these problems.
 - Cleaned up the WarpOS version, fixing some potential problems that
   could happen when an error occurred.
 - Minor code optimizations.
 - The installer now allows the destination of datatype files to be
   changed.

@{b}44.24@{ub} (24.9.2001)

 - Added support for files containing non-standard data, preceding the
   JFIF header.
 - WarpOS version reworked, now working in a fundamentally different way,
   to completely banish any possibility of cache conflicts - it also
   brings a speed increase of 2%.
 - Minor speedups for the 68k and MorphOS versions.
 - Fixed a bug which could cause a system deadlock if the dither control
   or pen precision options were enabled when using picture.datatype V44
   or higher.
 - Optimizations made to the dispatch engine.

@{b}44.23@{ub} (17.8.2001)

 - Added @{"greyscale output" link "Prefs" 92} mode option.
 - Fixed bug in memory manager, which could have caused crashes under
   certain low memory conditions.
 - Now supports the PDTA_GetNumPictures and PDTA_WhichPicture tags.
 - Discovered a bug in the CyberGraphX picture.datatype, concerning
   error numbers which would have resulted in an unknown error being
   reported by application software if bitmap allocation failed - added
   workaround.

@{b}44.22@{ub} (24.7.2001)

 - Added a workaround to the WarpOS version to stop the Exec memory list
   getting trashed if/when the datatype is flushed from memory, due to a
   bug in VBCC 0.8.
 - Added French strings to the installer.

@{b}44.21@{ub} (17.7.2001)

 - Fixed bug in the JPEG descriptor file, which caused some types of
   file not to be recognized.
 - Added support for various webcam images that weren't recognized before,
   including images from the NASA site.
 - Further optimizations to the memory management code.
 - PowerPC versions recompiled with VBCC 0.8.

@{b}44.20@{ub} (12.4.2001)

 - Improved YCCK to RGB colour conversion routine (Adobe images using
   the YCCK colour space should now look much closer to the original
   image).
 - Added RGB colour conversion support for Adobe images using the CMYK
   colour space.

@{b}44.19@{ub} (4.4.2001)

 - Added an optional 8-bit output mode for non-graphics card users, with a
   number of dithering and quality settings, which produces a much better
   image than the dithering method currently offered by picture.datatype.
 - Added options to control the precision/quality of pen allocations for
   when an image is displayed on a palette-based display (8-bit).
 - Added Spanish strings to the installer.

@{b}44.18@{ub} (15.3.2001)

 - Made @{"fast integer DCT method" link "Prefs" 0} available (approx 10% faster on 68k), and
   added a switch to toggle @{"fancy upsampling" link "Prefs" 0}.
 - Added preferences options to configure the OS3.5/3.9 @{"dithering control" link "Prefs" 0}
   feature.
 - Improved the memory management routines in all versions, bringing a
   small performance advantage for larger images on 68k (about 2% faster)
 - The 68k versions could crash if the JPEG stream was corrupt (bug
   introduced in v44.15) - fixed.

@{b}44.17@{ub} (19.2.2001)

 - The dithering disabler feature (for when the OS3.5/3.9 picture.datatype
   is in use on 15/16-bit displays) was flawed, since it only worked with
   images that were eventually attached to windows (e.g. Multiview). Now
   dithering will be disabled in all other cases too (e.g. Workbench /
   DOpus backdrops).

@{b}44.16@{ub} (12.1.2001)

 - Fixed a bug in the new startup code, which caused images not to be
   loaded in some cases - e.g. IPrefs failing to load WB backdrops.
 - The 68020-040 versions were completely broken in the previous release -
   forgot to rebuild one of the link libraries.
 - The 68k versions are faster again - moreorless back to the speed they
   were in 44.14.

@{b}44.15@{ub} (9.1.2001)

 - Recoded much of the startup code, with libraries now not being opened
   on the ramlib context (after advice from H&P)
 - Modified internal structure of the WarpOS version, to totally safeguard
   against cache conflicts (may have been causing rare random crashes)
 - All WarpOS benchmarks recomputed, since WarpOS V5 is a little bit
   faster than V4 (this datatype is upto 5% faster as a result)
 - Added benchmarks for MorphOS
 - Unfortunately, due to all the internal changes, the 68k version is now
   a little bit slower (only about 1%) than before

@{b}44.14@{ub} (7.9.2000)

 - 68k version is now a little bit faster (1-4% depending on the image).
 - Fixed bug in the previous release which caused all versions not to work
   with the P96 picture.datatype.

@{b}44.13@{ub} (2.9.2000)

 - Added a MorphOS native version and 68k version (in 020, 030, 040 and
   060 flavours) to accompany the original WarpOS version
 - Fixed bug which could case crashes under low memory conditions.

@{b}44.12@{ub} (2.8.2000)

 - Around 10% faster decoding of most images!
 - Recompiled with VBCC 0.7d beta, which gives a slight performance
   increase and smaller program binaries.
 - Tweaked compiler optimization options and increased disk i/o buffer for
   enhanced performance.
 - Improved the datafile descriptor file recognition code - it's faster
   now, and is able to detect more of the rarer types on JPEG file.
 - Recomputed all @{"benchmarks" link "Speed" 0}, to ensure correctness after a change in my
   test environment (test files are now on a different HD, due to a
   semi-fatal HD crash on the old partition).

@{b}44.11@{ub} (7.5.2000)

 - Made the descriptor less pedantic, so it will now match JFIF files
   starting with any standard marker type - i.e. less common,
   unidentifiable, types of JPEG file should now be recognized too.
 - Minor optimizations and code changes.

@{b}44.10@{ub} (5.3.2000)

 - Descriptor now recognizes JPEG's saved by Graphic Workshop for Windows.
 - Very minor code changes.

@{b}44.9@{ub} (8.2.2000)

 - Fixed a problem in the error cleanup code, which caused a PPC crash
   after decoding some corrupt JPEG files.

@{b}44.8@{ub} (4.2.2000)

 - Added support for images using the Adobe YCCK format.
 - Descriptor now recognizes Photoshop 3.0/5.2 JPEG file variations.

@{b}44.7@{ub} (22.1.2000)

 - Fixed possible deadlock case (caused everything to freeze/lock-up)
   which usually only occurred when lots of images were being decoded
   simultaneously.

@{b}44.6@{ub} (15.1.2000)

 - Rewrote parts of the descriptor code, so that it still works if
   other datatypes have messed with the current file position.  Should
   also be faster and more efficient.
 - Now able to decode EXIF thumbnail images.
 - Minor code changes.
 - The installer will now remove any JFIF descriptor files.

@{b}44.5@{ub} (9.1.2000)

 - When the OS3.5 picture.datatype is in use, dithering is now switched
   off (only) if the image is to be rendered to a 15/16-bit screen,
   resulting in much higher performance, with negligable quality loss.
 - Enhanced descriptor file to detect EXIF and Photoshop JPEG file
   variations.
 - Fixed bug in error handling.
 - Dispatcher now performs some extra functions, which may quash the
   stability problems that some users have experienced.

@{b}44.4@{ub} (5.1.2000)

 - Fixed silly bug new to v44.3 which caused a lot of images to be
   rendered with half the vertical resolution (i.e. every other line was
   left out and the rest were doubled), resulting in blocky images.
 - Ironically, fixing the above bug enabled the optimizations that I had
   originally intended: 30-50% faster for colour images, and around 100%
   faster for greyscale images!
 - Reverted to my simpler and less hungry asynchronous engine, as the
   new engine in 44.3 no longer offers an advantage with the above
   optimizations in place. [after release this was found to solve major
   stability problems that some users experienced with v44.3]
 - Corrected akJFIF WarpUp @{"benchmarks" link "Speed" 0}.

@{b}44.3@{ub} (3.1.2000)

 - At least 35% faster overall (upto 60% faster in many cases!), with
   no loss in the output image quality.
 - Enhanced descriptor file to detect more JPEG file formats.
 - Now uses asynchronous i/o routines which has made things a little bit
   faster overall, but will be most noticable on large (low compression)
   files and/or slower media.
 - Improved error handling.
 - Added @{"Speed" link "Speed" 0} section to this documentation.

@{b}44.2@{ub} (18.12.1999)

 - Now at least 10-25% faster (depending on the JPEG file) after
   optimizations and tweaking libjpeg settings.
 - Greyscale jpegs are now displayed if using the OS 3.5 or P96
   picture.datatype (only worked with the CGX one in v44.1).
 - Fixed little bug in the lib init (wasn't setting the revision number).

@{b}44.1@{ub} (15.12.1999)

 - Initial release.
@endnode

